WEBVTT

00:00.100 --> 00:02.609
<b>1x15 - Malefactor</b>

00:02.810 --> 00:05.312
The Olde Belwood Days
festival is the first personal

00:05.380 --> 00:07.681
appearance I've done in months.

00:07.749 --> 00:10.684
I can't find my name on here anywhere.

00:10.752 --> 00:14.655
Ben, I know you are
famous through much of the universe,

00:14.656 --> 00:18.559
but it does not seem right for a
Plumber to seek personal celebrity.

00:18.475 --> 00:20.642
Rook, Plumber.
Ben, heroic dude.

00:20.710 --> 00:22.323
If people want to shower me with

00:22.358 --> 00:24.571
attention, who am I
to stand in their way?

00:24.640 --> 00:26.542
<i>Ben Tennyson.</i>

00:27.610 --> 00:30.159
Natalie Alvarez, deputy
director, Belwood parks and

00:30.195 --> 00:33.314
recreation, and the event
organizer for this little shindig.

00:33.349 --> 00:34.744
We spoke on the phone.

00:34.780 --> 00:38.133
I'm glad you and your sidekick
could join us here today.

00:38.169 --> 00:40.130
- Sidekick?
- I wanted to get

00:40.165 --> 00:42.396
Kangaroo commando for
this year's festival.

00:42.432 --> 00:45.861
But the kids were all
"Ben 10, Ben 10," don't you know?

00:45.896 --> 00:48.395
Oh, man. Kangaroo
commando would've been sweet!

00:48.431 --> 00:50.361
Oh, I'm sure you'll be fine.

00:50.397 --> 00:54.963
We're on a tight schedule,
so if you'll just follow me...

00:56.699 --> 01:00.997
- That, of course, is the bell.
- The bell?

01:01.032 --> 01:03.765
<i>The world's largest wooden
sleigh bell to commemorate</i>

01:03.800 --> 01:06.031
<i>the laplanders who
founded Belwood in 1638.</i>

01:06.100 --> 01:10.832
Hand-carved from solid walnut,
it weighs over 3,000 pounds.

01:10.867 --> 01:14.665
- Bell. Wood.
- So, Ms. Alvarez, I know

01:14.734 --> 01:18.533
it's probably just some huge
typo or something, but I can't

01:18.568 --> 01:20.201
seem to find my name on here.

01:20.237 --> 01:23.936
- Hmm? Oh, yes.
- I mean, it's kind of

01:23.971 --> 01:27.206
weird, since I'm the
guest of honor and all.

01:28.841 --> 01:31.640
There's got to be some
kind of mistake, lady.

01:31.676 --> 01:33.442
I'm Ben Tennyson, superhero.

01:33.477 --> 01:36.010
Saved the world, like, a billion times.

01:36.045 --> 01:38.745
And the kids want a chance to dunk you.

01:38.814 --> 01:41.480
All proceeds go to charity.
Thanks again.

01:41.515 --> 01:43.848
This is ridiculous.
I'm out of here.

01:43.883 --> 01:46.450
Whoa!

01:50.554 --> 01:52.688
It is for charity.

01:57.355 --> 01:57.921
<i>♪ Ben 10 ♪</i>

01:57.990 --> 01:59.623
<i>♪ he's a kid,
and he wants to have fun ♪</i>

01:59.658 --> 02:02.260
<i>♪ but when you need a superhero,
he gets the job done ♪</i>

02:02.296 --> 02:02.794
<i>♪ Ben 10 ♪</i>

02:02.829 --> 02:04.796
<i>♪ with a device that he wears on his arm ♪</i>

02:04.831 --> 02:07.098
<i>♪ he can change his shape and
save the world from harm ♪</i>

02:07.168 --> 02:09.435
<i>♪ when trouble's taking place ♪
♪ he gets right in its face ♪</i>

02:09.470 --> 02:10.804
<i>♪ Ben 10 ♪</i>

02:11.839 --> 02:14.275
<i>♪ when lives are on the line ♪
♪ it's hero time ♪</i>

02:14.310 --> 02:15.542
<i>♪ Ben 10 ♪</i>

02:16.736 --> 02:19.802
<i><font color=#ca> sync & correction by f1nc0
~ addic7ed.com ~ </font></i>

02:23.973 --> 02:27.223
Do Big Chil... no, wait no.

02:27.224 --> 02:28.849
Brainstorm!

02:35.884 --> 02:39.489
<i>Oh, sure. Now the Omnitrix
gives me what I want.</i>

02:44.524 --> 02:46.591
<i>Out of my way, dweebs.</i>

02:48.000 --> 02:54.074
